{"chunk_id": "1aa008b1-1989-4f6b-b90a-866d6948e8ff", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 189, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "Health Benefits of Physical Activity /c63Controls body weight and composition. /c63Reduces risk chronic diseases, such as Type 2 diabetes, high blood pressure, heart disease, osteoporosis, arthritis and certain types of cancers. /c63Builds strong muscles, bones and joints. /c63Improves flexibility. /c63Wards off depression. /c63Improves mood, sense of well-being and self esteem. Regard movement as an opportunity and not an inconvenience Children and teenagers need at least 60 minutes of physical activity every day. In the case of pregnant women 30 minutes or more of moderate-intensity physical activity every day is recommended. However, it should be undertaken in consultation with the physician. Like others, geriatric population also will be benefitted considerably by physical activity,", "embedding": [-0.038632605224847794, 0.020084038376808167, 0.007480549160391092, 0.03660539537668228, -0.03661135956645012, 0.11287061870098114, -0.03222255781292915, 0.008823767304420471, -0.04542234167456627, -0.01633537746965885, 0.010025246068835258, -0.01604400761425495, -0.10937764495611191, -0.07746617496013641, 0.08776453882455826, 0.011227301321923733, 0.05927900969982147, -6.283656693994999e-05, -0.0011797021143138409, 0.07982372492551804, -0.07188250124454498, -0.009008477441966534, 0.096737340092659, 0.07988160103559494, -0.03007357008755207, -0.007922994904220104, -0.010691505856812, 0.02801945060491562, 0.02066442184150219, 0.05830775201320648, 8.822870586300269e-05, 0.0833713710308075, 0.025423448532819748, 0.05137406289577484, -0.09522741287946701, 0.0659254640340805, 0.016238464042544365, -0.05144547298550606, -0.07412419468164444, -0.008923018351197243, -0.01551325898617506, -0.001993825426325202, 0